### addNewBlock() {#afbcff91139fc89e3e8c0dda857e7b128}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void LiveVariables::addNewBlock (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &#42; BB, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &#42; DomBB, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &#42; SuccBB)</>}>
addNewBlock - Add a new basic block BB between DomBB and SuccBB.

addNewBlock - Add a new basic block BB as an empty succcessor to DomBB.

All variables that are live out of DomBB and live into SuccBB will be marked as passing live through BB. This method assumes that the machine code is still in SSA form.

All variables that are live out of DomBB will be marked as passing live through BB.

### addNewBlock() {#afc347ae9e7fcba69b04162d7b4a73635}

<MemberDefinition

Recompute liveness from scratch for a virtual register <code>Reg</code> that is known to have a single def that dominates all uses.

This can be useful after removing some uses of <code>Reg</code>. It is not necessary for the whole machine function to be in SSA form.
